%S A394554 1,1,2,3,7,13,32,70,173,435,1142,2908,7889,21051,56684,155661,427795
%N A394554 Degree of the minimal polynomial of the symmetry-reduced transfer matrix for 4-coloring of n X L grid graphs.
%C A394554 For q >= 5, the recurrence order exactly matches the number of Motzkin paths up to reversal (OEIS A378941). However, for the four-color problem (q=4), a periodic dimensional collapse occurs in the minimal polynomial degree when the grid height n is a multiple of three. This collapse is mathematically driven by the semisimplicity breaking of the Temperley-Lieb algebra at the critical Beraha number B_infinity = 4. At this limit, the loop fugacity is beta = 2, generating a nontrivial radical (null states) that forces the transfer matrix to become defective. In the continuous limit governed by a Logarithmic Conformal Field Theory (LCFT) with central charge c = -2, nilpotent zero-modes act as algebraic bridges, coupling independent states into degenerate Jordan blocks and shearing the degree away from A378941. Non-linear scaling thresholds (e.g., n=15) exhibit second-order interference, causing massive indecomposable modules and cascading local degeneracies.
%H A394554 Yi-Zhong Wang, <a href="https://osf.io/wr7g2/files/r42k3">A Mathematical Framework for the Recurrence Order of Chromatic Polynomials in Grid Graphs: Symmetry Reduction, Beraha Numbers, and LCFT</a>, 2026.
%H A394554 Yi-Zhong Wang, <a href="https://github.com/ReddiFSH2007/4-Coloring-Recurrence-Order-/tree/main">4-Coloring-Recurrence-Order</a>, C++ program.
%F A394554 For grid height n, the theoretical maximum recurrence order is (1/2) * (M_{n-1} + S_{n-1}), where M represents Motzkin numbers and S represents strictly symmetric Motzkin paths. The actual sequence a(n) deviates negatively from this formula when n is a multiple of 3 due to first-order and higher-order interference triggered by nilpotent zero-modes.
%e A394554 At non-resonant scales such as n=10, the recurrence rigorously binds to A378941, yielding a(10) = 435.
%e A394554 At n=9, the theoretical A378941 value is 179, but first-order interference manifests, yielding a drop of 6 and resulting in a(9) = 173.
%e A394554 At n=15, second-order interference causes the anomaly to drastically diverge, shedding 508 dimensions to yield a(15) = 56684.
